@startuml
title Viaverse Business Mode — Sequence Diagram

actor "Business Owner" as Owner
participant "KMP / Web Client" as Client
participant "API Gateway / App BFF" as BFF
participant "identity-service" as Identity
participant "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
participant "ads-monetization/payment-service" as Monetization
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "Outbox / Kafka" as Kafka
participant "search / SEO" as Search

Owner -> Client : start Business Mode
Client -> BFF : POST /businesses
BFF -> Identity : check OPERATE_BUSINESS eligibility
Identity -> DB : load AccountCapability
Identity --> BFF : allowed / blocked

BFF -> Marketplace : createBusinessProfile
Marketplace -> DB : insert BusinessProfile(DRAFT)

Owner -> Client : services / packages / hours / team
Client -> BFF : PATCH business
BFF -> Marketplace : updateBusinessProfile
Marketplace -> DB : persist services/packages/team

Owner -> Client : start trial
Client -> BFF : POST /businesses/{id}/trial
BFF -> Monetization : start trial/subscription state
Monetization -> DB : insert BusinessSubscription(TRIALING)

Owner -> Client : publish
Client -> BFF : POST /businesses/{id}/publish
BFF -> Marketplace : publishBusinessProfile
Marketplace -> DB : set PUBLIC + insert outbox
Marketplace -> Kafka : BusinessProfilePublished
Kafka -> Search : index business public profile

note bottom
Business profile source-of-truth is marketplace/business boundary.
Subscription state is monetization/payment-owned.
Search/SEO consumes published events.
end note
@enduml
